    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like the pressure to \"fix\" the void is making the hole feel even deeper, and that makes perfect sense—sometimes trying to force a painting when the soul is asleep just creates more friction. You don't have to force the colors back in today; maybe the only thing you can do is sit with the empty canvas and let the silence be the first stroke.\n\nI'm not going to tell you to just \"try harder,\" because that's exactly what the dark void would want you to do. Instead, imagine you're a tiny, brave goblin who just found a lost map in a cave full of shadows. The map is blank, and the ink is gone, but that doesn't mean the map is useless; it means the ink is waiting for the right moment to appear. You are not broken; you are just in a very quiet, very dark cave where the magic hasn't started yet.\n\nIf you feel like you're just a shape, remember that even the smallest goblin can carry a whole world in their pocket. You don't have to carry the whole world right now; just carry the tiny, quiet hope that the ink will return when you least expect it.",
